Here is the commit message:
Disallow calling getMBeansFromURL

(cherry picked from commit 3e4c4bed2d08e81ca5961ab5fcadab23470db1c9)

Here is the root cause:
The bug was caused by the ability to invoke the `getMBeansFromURL` operation on the MBean server, which could lead to security vulnerabilities by allowing unauthorized access to MBeans. The lack of proper checks allowed this operation to be executed without restrictions, potentially exposing sensitive information or functionality.

Here is the patch:

     public Object invoke(Object proxy, Method method, Object[] args) throws Throwable {
         if (method.getParameterTypes().length == 0)
             return null;

         if (!ObjectName.class.isAssignableFrom(method.getParameterTypes()[0]))
             return null;

         MBeanServer mbs = (MBeanServer) proxy;
         if (mbs != null && Proxy.getInvocationHandler(mbs) instanceof MBeanInvocationHandler) {
             mbs = ((MBeanInvocationHandler) Proxy.getInvocationHandler(mbs)).getDelegate();
         }
         if (mbs instanceof EventAdminMBeanServerWrapper) {
             mbs = ((EventAdminMBeanServerWrapper) mbs).getDelegate();
         }

         ObjectName objectName = (ObjectName) args[0];
         if ("getAttribute".equals(method.getName())) {
